frameDefinitions: An Assailant, a group of armed forces, surrounds the Victim, a military location and the people within it, in an attempt to cut the Victim off from the outside, with the goal of either forcing their surrender or weakening them so that an invasion would be successful.
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
The Agent is assigned to a Post where he or she performs a task associated with that Post.
Words in this frame describe acts in violation of a legal code.
The Invader enters a Land in an aggressive attempt to cripple or dominate its people and its government.
frameExamples: Towards the end of the summer, a great English host <t>besieged</t> the Danish fort of Tempsford and took it, killing the last Danish king of East Anglia.
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
He was accused of <t><fex name='Offense'>hijacking</fex></t> a tour bus full of people.
In August 1990 ,Iraq was <t>invading</t> Kuwait , which led to the Gulf war .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Assailant</fen> is a group of armed forces (or, metonymically, their commander or the organization they represent) that encircles, surrounds, or otherwise cuts off the Beseiged in an attempt to force surrender.
The <fen>Victim</fen> is the fortification or geopolitical entity that is being attacked.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role is the being or entity that is injured by the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is assigned to a <fen>Post</fen> to perform a task involving a <fen>Salient_entity</fen>.
The <fen>Post</fen> is a location or station assigned to the <fen>Agent</fen> where a task or tasks are to be performed.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> is centrally involved in the task the <fen>Agent</fen> is assigned to perform. It is normally located at the <fen>Post</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> works at the <fen>Post</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> staffs the <fen>Post</fen>.
The illegal act.
This role denotes the person or entity that is badly affected by the <fen>Offense</fen>.
The individual who commits the Offense
The political area that is being crippled by the <fen>Invader</fen>'s entry.
The army or other self-directed entity that is entering the <fen>Land</fen> in a hostile manner.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Invader</fen> invades <fen>Land</fen>.
This role identifies the location where the <fen>Invader</fen> invades the <fen>Land</fen>.

<fex>The mysterious fighter</fex> attacked the guardsmen with a sabre.
